Interface ObjectFactory<T>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of the objects that this factory will create and reset.
All Known Implementing Classes:
BulletFactory
public interface ObjectFactory<T>
A generic interface for creating and resetting objects, typically used in object pooling mechanisms. This interface defines two key methods: - create() for creating a new instance of the object. - reset(Object) for resetting the state of an existing object, making it reusable.

  • Method Details

    • create

      T create()
      Creates a new instance of the object. This method is called when a new object is needed in the object pool.
      Returns:
      A new instance of type T.

    • reset

      void reset(T obj)
      Resets the state of an object, preparing it for reuse. This method is typically called before returning the object to the pool to ensure it is in a consistent and reusable state.
      Parameters:
      obj - The object to reset. The implementation should ensure all fields and states of the object are reverted to their default values.
